# RoboLedger V5.2.24: High-Fidelity Header & COA Restoration

This update targets the core ergonomics of the transaction grid, sharpening the visual structure and restoring the essential Chart of Accounts (COA) workflow.

## 📐 Grid Header Fidelity
The rainbow header is now sharper and more professional, with zero text truncation.
- [x] **Sharpened Dividers**: Header dividers increased to **60% white**; body cell dividers added at **10% black** for perfect vertical alignment.
- [x] **Zero Truncation**: Expanded the **Ref#** (95px), **Source** (85px), and **Debit/Credit** (110px) columns to give titles and sorting arrows ample breathing room.
- [x] **Wall Street Typography**: Refined letter-spacing and font-size for a high-density, professional finish.

## 🛠️ COA Editor Restoration
The "Account" column dropdown is fully functional and wired to the ledger.
- [x] **Robust Select Editor**: Switched to a high-density `select` editor that appears instantly on click.
- [x] **Categorized Grouping**: Accounts are logically grouped by type (Assets, Liabilities, etc.) with consistent icons.
- [x] **Forensic Persistence**: Any manual category selection is instantly saved to the forensic ledger via the new recursive [save()](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/ledger.core.js#156-162) wire.

## 🏛️ Phase 50: Logic & Metadata Hardening
- [x] **Smart Search**: Integrated live forensic searching across descriptions and references.
- [x] **Bidirectional Ref Sync**: Changing an account's Ref# instantly updates all UI pills and grid badges.
- [x] **Metadata Recovery**: Unified canonical property naming (`accountNumber`) to ensure institution and transit data always display in the action bar.

